Support NDOH Health Facility Standard Branch, National Immunisation Programme, provincial health authorities and immunisation stakeholders on strengthening immunisation Supply Chain and Logistics Management (iSCM):
i) Technical assistance to implement the CCEOP-ODP and HSS2-iSCM activities including distribution, installation & commissioning of CCEs at health facilities in provinces, monitoring the functionality of the equipment guided by the CCEOP Project Managemet Team (PMT), capacity building and mentoring of the biomedical technicians on CCE maintenance in the provinces;
ii) Effective functioning of National Logistics Working Group (NLWG) to guide and monitor the implementation of the immunisation supply chain logistics management (iSCLM) and strengtheing the iSCLM systems;
iii) Technical assistance to ensure Effective Vaccine Management (EVM) at all levels of supply chain and develop semi-annual Cold Chain Equipment (CCE) inventory;
iv) Tehcnical assistance to procurement services of vaccines, cold chain and other immunisation supplies.
v) Monitoring iSCM data management guided by the newly developped SOPs to improve vaccine distribution, temperature monitoirng with low and high alarm, stock management, and wastage.

